  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Behavior: if the `searchParameters` props is updated, nothing will happen because `searchParameters` are not updated internally. \r\n\r\nThere's two things here: \r\n\r\n* we never update the `searchParameters` property once `InstantSearch` is mounted. It means that a user will never be able to change them once `InstantSearch` is mounted. \r\n* when `InstantSearch` is uncontrolled (meaning that the state is not handle externally), we do not perform a new search. So even if we were updating the `searchParameters`, nothing would happen.\r\n\r\n**Solutions to achieve this use-case**: add a VirtualWidget with the `slug` param as the defaultRefinement.  \r\n\r\n@vvo, @bobylito: wdyt about this? If we don't allow the searchParameters to be updated, maybe we should be clear about that in our documentation. Also, VirtualWidgets can be used in many different ways, I guess we can improve the guide about them :) \r\n\r\n",
