    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Solutions to achieve this use-case: add a VirtualWidget with the slug param as the defaultRefinement.\r\n\r\nThis solution looks like a workaround (good one). But still in react I would expect that updating any prop on InstantSearch would actually do what I want: update the corresponding linked behaviors. What do you think?\r\n\r\nUltimately we might just have a state with:\r\n\r\n```\r\nsearchParameters: {\r\n  page: 0,\r\n  filters: ...\r\n  distinct: ...\r\n},\r\nwidgets: {\r\n  menu: {\r\n    brands: 'Sony'\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut in the meantime, what about we allow updating searchParameters?\r\n\r\nAnd users will be able to update any searchParameters (sorry this is confusing, I am not really talking about SearchParameters from the helper here, just all API parameters that are not handled by widgets.)",
